Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significantly elevated creatinine in both serum and blood, indicating impaired renal function. Urinalysis reveals marked proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, and abnormal urine appearance (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal), suggesting possible nephrotic syndrome or acute kidney injury with metabolic derangements. Blood glucose and HbA1c are normal, making diabetes less likely. Recommend urgent nephrology evaluation and further workup for underlying renal pathology.
